{
  "texts": [
    "Using the six graph-level characteristics of maps explained in section 2, we compared the maps produced by our system at several levels of iteration with the maps produced by humans (Table 4).",
    "As expected, the number of iterations is a key parameter: it determines the size of the map and hence affects other metrics.",
    "Overall, the system can create maps that closely resemble human maps in some, but not all, characteristics.",
    "Density can often be matched, hence the system is parsimonious in identifying causal statements, just as humans are selective when mapping a problem domain.",
    "The number of nodes can be matched if the document is long, but the number of edges tends to be too high."
  ]
}